    'tiktok.overviewTitle': 'Overview',
    'tiktok.overviewP1': 'By 2025, TikTok Shop held roughly 41% of Vietnam\'s e-commerce market, growing faster than almost any platform in the region. The numbers looked strong. What they didn\'t show was the structural problem sitting underneath: a platform that had mastered attention was struggling to convert that attention into anything durable.',
    'tiktok.overviewP2': 'This project analyzed TikTok Shop\'s integrated marketing communications strategy and proposed a campaign for the 30/4–1/5 national holiday. My contribution was the communications audit, Chapter 2.2, covering market context, target audience architecture, messaging structure, campaign results, and the four structural problems the growth figures were masking.',
    'tiktok.marketTitle': 'Market & Strategic Analysis',
    'tiktok.marketP1': 'Vietnam\'s e-commerce market crossed $25B in 2024, growing 18–25% annually. Social commerce, purchase behavior triggered by content rather than search, is growing at roughly 25% CAGR through 2027. TikTok Shop sits at the intersection of this shift: it doesn\'t compete on price or logistics. It competes on attention.',
    'tiktok.marketP2': 'The 3Cs analysis positioned TikTok Shop as a multi-sided platform where value comes from network effects: more buyers attract more sellers attract more creators, which generates more content, which drives more purchases. The competitive map showed TikTok Shop clearly differentiated from Shopee on one axis (content-driven vs. search-driven discovery) while still trailing on the trust and official-brand axis where Lazada\'s LazMall leads.',
    'tiktok.audienceTitle': 'Target Audience Architecture',
    'tiktok.audienceP1': 'TikTok Shop serves three simultaneous customer groups, each with different incentives.',
    'tiktok.audienceP2': 'Buyers (18–35, Gen Z and Millennials) are motivated by entertainment, social proof, and FOMO during livestreams. 62.8% of digital consumers purchase at least once per week.',
    'tiktok.audienceP3': 'Sellers, ranging from SMEs to established brands, use TikTok as an additional distribution channel and are increasingly squeezed as the market consolidates toward professional operators.',
    'tiktok.audienceP4': 'Creators and affiliates are the structural differentiator: they convert content into commerce and extend platform trust through personal credibility.',
    'tiktok.messagingTitle': 'Messaging Architecture',
    'tiktok.messagingP1': 'TikTok Shop\'s communications strategy operates on three pillars: Discover More, Shop with Entertainment, and Anyone Can Sell Anyone Can Earn. Together they form a single logic: Content to Emotion to Trust to Transaction. Each pillar targets a different conversion stage, and the creator ecosystem is what makes the chain hold together.',
    'tiktok.problemsTitle': 'Structural Communication Problems',
    'tiktok.problemsP1': 'Sale dependency: consumer perception of TikTok Shop is anchored to flash deals and discount events, weakening long-term brand equity.',
    'tiktok.problemsP2': 'Transactional behavior pattern: purchase spikes during sale events with low engagement outside them, limiting customer lifetime value.',
    'tiktok.problemsP3': 'Ecosystem value undertold: the platform has a genuinely differentiated content-commerce ecosystem but communicates it mostly through promotional mechanics, not brand narrative.',
    'tiktok.problemsP4': 'No social identity formed: high viral reach without building a stable brand personality that users identify with beyond \'cheap stuff on livestreams.\'',
    'tiktok.directionTitle': 'From Analysis to Direction',
    'tiktok.directionP1': 'The four structural problems converged on a single gap: TikTok Shop had built a highly effective distribution machine but not a brand. Users trusted individual creators. They didn\'t trust the platform itself.',
    'tiktok.directionP2': 'That gap was what the proposed 30/4–1/5 campaign was designed to address. Rather than another discount event, \'Tu Hao Moi Vung\' used regional identity and cultural pride as the mechanism for building a platform narrative that didn\'t need promotions to be compelling. The logic came directly from the audit: TikTok Shop\'s content ecosystem was already generating that kind of connection organically. The campaign made it intentional.',
    'tiktok.directionP3': 'The Amazon Prime Day case pointed at the same conclusion from a different angle: the most durable platform events aren\'t sales, they\'re identity moments. Prime Day doesn\'t feel like a discount. It feels like something Amazon members do. That was the model.',
